content.description: Start in the obvious chimney in the center of the wall. Once the chimney turns left here I have always continued straight through some cracks and face to an anchor at about 100 ft. a excellent line! I guess you can take hard left and follow a crack below the chinmey to an anchor or follow the chimney then crack and face to the top. I havent done these two other variations.

content.description: TSEFNEAB, Beanfest spelled backwards is the west facing wall near the stronghold dome. It does see a bit of later afternoon shade casted by the shadow of the Rockfellow. The wall is easily ID by its highly fractured face.
